    <h1>Logging Setup</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>We've chosen to use the log4net logging framework.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"LoggingSetup-Configuration">Configuration</h2>
<p>Log4net is configured through XML in the .config file of the executing p=
roject. A simple log4net block looks like this:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">  &lt;l=
og4net&gt;
    &lt;appender name=3D"ColoredConsoleAppender" type=3D"log4net.Appender.C=
oloredConsoleAppender"&gt;
      &lt;mapping&gt;
        &lt;level value=3D"ERROR" /&gt;
        &lt;foreColor value=3D"White" /&gt;
        &lt;backColor value=3D"Red, HighIntensity" /&gt;
      &lt;/mapping&gt;
      &lt;layout type=3D"log4net.Layout.PatternLayout"&gt;
        &lt;conversionPattern value=3D"%date [%2thread] %-5level %logger - =
%message%newline" /&gt;
      &lt;/layout&gt;
    &lt;/appender&gt;
    &lt;appender name=3D"RollingFileAppender" type=3D"log4net.Appender.Roll=
ingFileAppender"&gt;
      &lt;file value=3D"log.txt" /&gt;
      &lt;appendToFile value=3D"true" /&gt;
      &lt;immediateFlush value=3D"true" /&gt;
      &lt;rollingStyle value=3D"Size" /&gt;
      &lt;maxSizeRollBackups value=3D"10" /&gt;
      &lt;maximumFileSize value=3D"20MB" /&gt;
      &lt;staticLogFileName value=3D"true" /&gt;
      &lt;layout type=3D"log4net.Layout.PatternLayout"&gt;
        &lt;conversionPattern value=3D"%date [%2thread] %-5level %logger - =
%message%newline" /&gt;
      &lt;/layout&gt;
    &lt;/appender&gt;

    &lt;root&gt;
      &lt;level value=3D"ALL" /&gt;
      &lt;appender-ref ref=3D"ColoredConsoleAppender" /&gt;
      &lt;appender-ref ref=3D"RollingFileAppender" /&gt;
    &lt;/root&gt;
  &lt;/log4net&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>In this block, two appenders (output streams) are defined. The first wri=
tes all logging to the console, using colors. The seconds writes to a rolli=
ng list of files.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"LoggingSetup-Setup">Setup</h2>
<p>This section describes the different ways of logging that are used in pr=
oduction and how they're used.&nbsp;</p>
<p>We log in the following manners:</p>
<ol>
<li>To a central logging database. This database is called CentralLog, and =
has a table for each environment. For performance reasons, we log to this d=
atabase in batches of 100, meaning sometimes the latest logging messages ar=
en't yet present in the database.</li>
<li>To a (rolling) file. This log always contains the latest entries and is=
 used mainly to view the current state of the system without delay.&nbsp;</=
li>
<li>To a slack #logging channel. Only errors are logged on this channel. it=
's used to notify developers something went wrong.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>
